headline: Stryker (SYK) Raises Guidance As Sales Reach US$6 Billion In Strong Q2
summary: Stryker (SYK) has raised its earnings guidance for 2025, citing strong product demand and operational momentum, following a reported 11% increase in quarterly sales. This positive outlook, combined with FDA clearance for innovative products like the Incompass® Total Ankle System and OptaBlate BVN, may have supported a 3.84% share price increase over the last quarter.
